      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROSEBUD LASS (5) raced close to the lead before clearing out to score an effortless 4.5 lengths win over 1200m at this track last time. Will go forward and has plenty of upside. Should be in the finish again. LEAN ON ME (1) turned in a fine effort to win by half a length at this course and distance last start. Rates to go close again. BON'S A LAD (3) won fresh over 1000m then has been fourth last two. Yet to fire over 1200m bur rates highly on best and capable of being in the finish. CEE PEE ONE (7) returns from a layoff of five months. Worth noting he filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last time in work over 1100m at Darwin. Has found a suitable race and is worth including. THE BIG FREEZE (6) is capable and ready to win after two runs back.",
